A
\mathbb{N}
\nu(\frac{1}{2}n (n+1)) = n
\nu
\mathbb N\to A
n\mapsto \frac{n(n+1)}2
\begin{align} \frac{n(n+1)}2=\frac{m(m+1)}2&\implies n(n+1)=m(m+1)\\&\implies n^2-m^2+n-m=0\\&\implies (n-m)(n+m+1)=0\\&\implies n-m=0\lor n+m+1=0\implies n=m.\end{align}
